\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\b\loch\b Philippians 3:8-19}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0  Yea doubtless, and I count all things but loss for the excellency of the knowledge of Christ Jesus my Lord: for whom I have suffered the loss of all things, and do count them but dung, that I may win Christ, {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 9} And be found in him, not ha
ving mine own righteousness, which is of the law, but that which is through the faith of Christ, the righteousness which is of God by faith: {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 10} That I may know him, and the power of his resurrection, and the fellowship of his sufferings, being made conform
able unto his death; {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 11} If by any means I might attain unto the resurrection of the dead. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 12} Not as though I had already attained, either were already perfect: but I follow after, if that I may apprehend that for which also I am apprehended of Christ Jesus
. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 13} Brethren, I count not myself to have apprehended: but this one thing I do, forgetting those things which are behind, and reaching forth unto those things which are before, {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 14} I press toward the mark for the prize of the high calling of God in Christ J
esus. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 15} Let us therefore, as many as be perfect, be thus minded: and if in any thing ye be otherwise minded, God shall reveal even this unto you. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 16} Nevertheless, whereto we have already attained, let us walk by the same rule, let us mind the same thing. 
{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 17} Brethren, be followers together of me, and mark them which walk so as ye have us for an ensample. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 18} (For many walk, of whom I have told you often, and now tell you even weeping, that they are the enemies of the cross of Christ: {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 19} Whose end is destruct
ion, whose God is their belly, and whose glory is in their shame, who mind earthly things.)}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\b\loch\b Luke 7:31-35}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0  And the Lord said, Whereunto then shall I liken the men of this generation? and to what are they like? {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 32} They are like unto children sitting in the marketplace, and calling one to another, and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not d
anced; we have mourned to you, and ye have not wept. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 33} For John the Baptist came neither eating bread nor drinking wine; and ye say, He hath a devil. {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 34} The Son of man is come eating and drinking; and ye say, Behold a gluttonous man, and a winebibber, a f
riend of publicans and sinners! {\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 35} But wisdom is justified of all her children.}
