\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf1\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b Luke 7:31-34 }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b And the Lord said, Whereunto then shall I liken the men of this generation? and to what are they like? }{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 32}{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b  They are like unto children sitting in the marketplace, and calling one to another, and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not d
anced; we have mourned to you, and ye have not wept. }{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 33}{\cf1  }{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b For John the Baptist came neither eating bread nor drinking wine; and ye say, He hath a devil. }{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 34}{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b  The Son of man is come eating and drinking; and ye say, Behold a gluttonous man, and a winebibber, a f
riend of publicans and sinners!}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\af5\langfe255\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf1 The Lord is using a Jewish game of the time to ridicule the Pharisees. The game was played with two groups of children. One group would mourn and wail and the other would dance and play flutes. Each group would stay separate from the other. This doubtless 
was imitating the real funerals and celebrations they had seen.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 The Lord is exposing the Pharisee\'92s hypocrisy. They would not join with St John the Baptist, nor with Christ. The mourning children represent St John, who lived and austere life. The dancing children represent our Lord, who did not live such an austere lif
e in public, as St John did. The Pharisees held themselves from both, and ridiculed both their teachings and ways of life.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf0\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\cf1 Rightly might the Lord have also said to them: \'93Woe unto (you who) call evil good, and good evil; that put darkness for light, and light for darkness; that put bitter for sweet, and sweet for bitter! \'93}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs22\loch\f4\fs22  }{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 (Isa 5:20}{\cf1 ). Or He may well have said: \'93So then because
 thou art lukewarm, and neither cold nor hot, I will spue thee out of my mouth.\'94}{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f4\fs22\loch\f4\fs22  }{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\fs16\loch\f2\fs16 (Rev 3:16). }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\ul\ulc0\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b Luke 7:35}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\f2\b\loch\f2\b  But wisdom is justified of all her children}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch \'93}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 Wisdom\'94, is of course, Jesus Christ, and her children are those that believe in Christ, and follow His teachings. The Book of the Wisdom of Solomon, Proverbs and the Psalms especially contain references to \'93Wisdom\'94. In this passage, Jesus appropriates thi
s name for Himself. \'93Son of Man\'94 is another name He frequently used for himself (and just as \'93Wisdom\'94, this name occurs in the OT scriptures)}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\i0\b0 It is good to know the factual content of the scripture, but this is no good to our soul unless we apply it to ourselves. The admonition of the Lord to the Pharisees applies to many in our day. Can we with a straight face call ourselves the children of Wis
dom if we do not follow Christ completely? In our politically correct day, many falsehoods are called true and good things labeled as evil. Most people, including those who fancy themselves to be Christian, are heavily influenced by the opinions of the day
. These opinions, which are a mixture of good and evil, are held by those who neither mourn, nor dance. We must guard ourselves carefully from such opinions, because as we believe, so we live. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\cf1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\afs24\lang1033\ltrch\dbch\langfe1033\hich\fs24\lang1033\loch\fs24\lang1033 
